nTime = nLat

nTimemultiplier2 = 10

nSims = 100

m2eff = 1.
lenLat = 100.
nCols = 2

nyq = nLat//2
spec = nyq

alpha = 8
dx = lenLat/nLat
dk = 2.*np.pi/lenLat
dt = dx/alpha
dtout = dt*alpha

sim_location = lambda nT, nL, gam, m2, tem, phi, lam, sim: '/gpfs/dpirvu/thermal_bubbles/phi4_meffPS_t'+str(nT)+'_x'+str(nL)+'_gam'+str(gam)+'_m2{:.4f}'.format(m2)+'_temp{:.4f}'.format(tem)+'_phi0{:.4f}'.format(phi)+'_lamb{:.4f}'.format(lam)+'_sim'+str(sim)+'_fields.dat'
smoothen = lambda slice, sigma: np.fft.ifft(np.fft.fft(slice)*Filter(sigma))

def extract_sim(nT, nL, gam, m2, tem, phi, lam, sim):
    nTT = nT*(nTimemultiplier1 if gam != 1 else nTimemultiplier2)
    if sim == 0: print(nTT, nT, nL, gam, m2, tem, phi, lam)
    data = np.genfromtxt(sim_location(nTT, nL, gam, m2, tem, phi, lam, sim))
    return np.asarray([np.reshape(data[:,col], (nTT, nL))[-nL::] for col in range(nCols)])

# field spectrum
# prediction from lattice renormalization
freqs = np.fft.fftshift(np.fft.fftfreq(nLat, d=dx))*2*np.pi
norm = 1./ phi0 / np.sqrt(2.*lenLat)
omega = np.sqrt(freqs**2. + m2eff)

spectral_field = lambda tem: np.asarray([norm * np.sqrt(2./(np.exp(omega[k]/tem) - 1.)) / omega[k]**0.5 if k != nLat//2 else 0 for k in range(nLat)])
sigma0sq_th = lambda tem: np.sum( np.abs(spectral_field(tem))**2. )

V = lambda x, lam, gam: (0.5*m2eff*x**2. + lam*x**4./24.) if gam == 0. else (-0.5*m2eff*x**2. + lam*x**4./24.) if gam == 1. else (0.5*m2eff*x**2.)
VV = lambda x, lam, gam: (m2eff + 0.5*lam*x**2.) if gam == 0. else (-m2eff + 0.5*lam*x**2.) if gam == 1. else m2eff

th_masses = lambda lam, gam, tem: (-m2eff if gam == 1 else m2eff) + 0.5 * lam * sigma0sq_th(tem)

def remove_walls(lam, gam, temp, sim, win):
    simulation = all_data[temp][lam][gam][sim][0]
    simulation = simulation - np.mean(simulation)
    fftfld = np.fft.fftshift(np.fft.fft2(simulation))
    T, N = np.shape(fftfld)
    kk = np.fft.fftshift(np.fft.fftfreq(N, d=dx))*2*np.pi
    oo = np.fft.fftshift(np.fft.fftfreq(T, d=dtout))*2*np.pi
    KK, OO = np.meshgrid(kk,oo)

    p1, p2, p3 = 1., 1., 0.5
    coords = ((KK/p1)**2. - (OO/p2)**2. <= -(p3)**2.)
    fftfld = fftfld*coords
    return kk, oo, fftfld, np.fft.ifft2(np.fft.ifftshift(fftfld)).real[win:nTime-win, win:nLat-win], simulation[win:nTime-win, win:nLat-win]

# get mass best fit
omega_fit = lambda k, m: k**2. + m

def get_truncation_frequency(PowSpec, oo, kk):
    kselect = np.sort(kk[kk>0])[0]
    window_in_k = np.mean(PowSpec[:, kk==kselect], axis=1)[(np.in1d(oo,kk))&(oo>0)]
    smooth_window_in_k = gaussian_filter1d(window_in_k, sigma=0.5, mode='constant')
    minpeaks, properties = scs.find_peaks(-smooth_window_in_k, height=-max(smooth_window_in_k))
    minpeaks, height = minpeaks[0], -properties['peak_heights'][0]

    maxpeaks, properties = scs.find_peaks(smooth_window_in_k, height=min(smooth_window_in_k))
    return ([minpeaks, height] if minpeaks < maxpeaks[properties['peak_heights']==max(properties['peak_heights'])] else [0, 0])

def get_masses(bool, multiplier, lam, gam):
    masses = []
    for tem in range(len(list_temp)):
        PowSpec = np.mean(np.abs(np.fft.fftshift(np.fft.fft2(all_data[tem][lam][gam][:,0])))**2., axis=0)
        kk = np.fft.fftshift(np.fft.fftfreq(np.shape(PowSpec)[1], d=dx))*2*np.pi
        oo = np.fft.fftshift(np.fft.fftfreq(np.shape(PowSpec)[0], d=dtout))*2*np.pi
        KK, OO = np.meshgrid(kk,oo)
        
        if gam != 0:
            trunc_freq, trunc_amp = get_truncation_frequency(PowSpec, oo, kk)
        else:
            trunc_freq, trunc_amp = 0, 0.
        PowSpec = PowSpec*(np.abs(OO) >= oo[oo>0][trunc_freq])
        osccoords = np.argwhere(PowSpec > max(trunc_amp, np.mean(PowSpec) + multiplier * np.std(PowSpec)))

        popt, pcov = sco.curve_fit(omega_fit, kk[osccoords[:,1]], oo[osccoords[:,0]]**2.)
        if popt[-1] < 0: masses.append('nan')
        else: masses.append(popt[-1])

        if bool:
            lim = max(freqs)
            fig, ax = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize = (16, 4))
            ax[0].plot(kk[osccoords[:,1]], oo[osccoords[:,0]], 'o', ms=5, label='freqs')
            ax[0].plot(kk, np.sqrt(omega_fit(kk,*popt)), label=f'$T = %5.5f, m^2 = %5.5f$'%(list_temp[tem], popt[-1]))
            ax[0].set_xlim(-lim,lim)
            ax[0].set_ylim(0,lim)
            ax[0].axhline(popt[-1], color='darkgray', ls=':', label='best fit')
            ax[0].axhline(m2eff, color='darkgray', ls='-.', label='potential mass')
            ax[0].legend()

            lim = 3
            ax[1].plot(kk, np.sqrt(omega_fit(kk,*popt)), color = 'y', label=f'$T = %5.5f, m^2 = %5.5f$'%(list_temp[tem], popt[-1]))
            im = ax[1].imshow(PowSpec, aspect='auto', interpolation='none', origin='lower', extent=[kk[0],kk[-1],oo[0],oo[-1]])
            clb = plt.colorbar(im, ax = ax[1])
            ax[1].set_title(f'$T = %5.2f, \gamma = %5.2f, \lambda = %5.2f$'%(list_temp[tem], list_gamma[gam], list_lamb[lam]))
            ax[1].set_xlabel(r'$\bar{k}$')
            ax[1].set_ylabel(r'$\bar{\omega_k}$')
            ax[1].set_xlim(-lim,lim)
            ax[1].set_ylim(0,lim)
            ax[1].axvline(0, color='white', ls=':')
            ax[1].axhline(0, color='white', ls=':')
            [i.legend() for i in ax]
            plt.show()
    return masses

def get_pspec(lam, gam, tem, thresh):
    PowSpec = np.mean(np.abs(np.fft.fftshift(np.fft.fft2(all_data[tem][lam][gam][:,0])))**2., axis=0)
    kk = np.fft.fftshift(np.fft.fftfreq(np.shape(PowSpec)[1], d=dx))*2*np.pi
    oo = np.fft.fftshift(np.fft.fftfreq(np.shape(PowSpec)[0], d=dtout))*2*np.pi

    pick_freq_window = (kk>0)&(kk<thresh)
    pick_omega = np.sort(oo[oo>0])[0]
    return np.mean(PowSpec[:, kk==pick_freq_window], axis=1)[(np.in1d(oo,kk))&(oo>0)], PowSpec[oo==pick_omega, kk>0], oo[oo>0], kk[kk>0]

# get mass best fit
omega_fit = lambda k, m: k**2. + m

def get_truncation_frequency(PowSpec, oo, kk):
    kselect = np.sort(kk[kk>0])[0]
    window_in_k = np.mean(PowSpec[:, kk==kselect], axis=1)[(np.in1d(oo,kk))&(oo>0)]
    smooth_window_in_k = gaussian_filter1d(window_in_k, sigma=0.5, mode='constant')
    minpeaks, properties = scs.find_peaks(-smooth_window_in_k, height=-max(smooth_window_in_k))
    minpeaks, height = minpeaks[0], -properties['peak_heights'][0]

    maxpeaks, properties = scs.find_peaks(smooth_window_in_k, height=min(smooth_window_in_k))
    return ([minpeaks, height] if minpeaks < maxpeaks[properties['peak_heights']==max(properties['peak_heights'])] else [0, 0])

def get_masses_seps(bool, multiplier, lam, gam):
    fullmasses, remasses, immasses = [], [], []
    for tem in range(len(list_temp)):
        fullPowSpec, rePowSpec, imPowSpec = [], [], []
        for sim in range(nSims):
            fftfield = np.fft.fftshift(np.fft.fft2(all_data[tem][lam][gam][sim][0], norm='ortho'))
            fullPowSpec.append(np.abs(fftfield)**2.)
            rePowSpec.append(np.abs(fftfield.real)**2.)
            imPowSpec.append(np.abs(fftfield.imag)**2.)
        fullPowSpec, rePowSpec, imPowSpec = np.mean(fullPowSpec, axis = 0), np.mean(rePowSpec, axis = 0), np.mean(imPowSpec, axis = 0)
        T, N = np.shape(fullPowSpec)
        kk = np.fft.fftshift(np.fft.fftfreq(N, d=dx))*2*np.pi
        oo = np.fft.fftshift(np.fft.fftfreq(T, d=dtout))*2*np.pi
        KK, OO = np.meshgrid(kk,oo)

        if gam != 0:
            full_trunc_freq, full_trunc_amp = get_truncation_frequency(fullPowSpec, oo, kk)
            re_trunc_freq, re_trunc_amp = get_truncation_frequency(rePowSpec, oo, kk)
            im_trunc_freq, im_trunc_amp = get_truncation_frequency(imPowSpec, oo, kk)
        else:
            full_trunc_freq, full_trunc_amp, re_trunc_freq, re_trunc_amp, im_trunc_freq, im_trunc_amp = 0, 0., 0, 0., 0, 0.

        fullPowSpec = fullPowSpec*(np.abs(OO) >= oo[oo>0][full_trunc_freq])
        rePowSpec = rePowSpec*(np.abs(OO) >= oo[oo>0][re_trunc_freq])
        imPowSpec = imPowSpec*(np.abs(OO) >= oo[oo>0][im_trunc_freq])

        fullosccoords = np.argwhere(fullPowSpec > max(full_trunc_amp, np.mean(fullPowSpec) + multiplier * np.std(fullPowSpec)))
        reosccoords = np.argwhere(rePowSpec > max(re_trunc_amp, np.mean(rePowSpec) + multiplier * np.std(rePowSpec)))
        imosccoords = np.argwhere(imPowSpec > max(im_trunc_amp, np.mean(imPowSpec) + multiplier * np.std(imPowSpec)))

        fullmasses.append(sco.curve_fit(omega_fit, kk[fullosccoords[:,1]], oo[fullosccoords[:,0]]**2.)[0])
        remasses.append(sco.curve_fit(omega_fit, kk[reosccoords[:,1]], oo[reosccoords[:,0]]**2.)[0])
        immasses.append(sco.curve_fit(omega_fit, kk[imosccoords[:,1]], oo[imosccoords[:,0]]**2.)[0])

        coords = np.asarray([fullosccoords, reosccoords, imosccoords])
        PowSpecs = np.asarray([fullPowSpec, rePowSpec, imPowSpec])
        allMasses = np.asarray([fullmasses, remasses, immasses])
        title = ['Full, ', 'Real, ', 'Imag, ']
        if bool:
            fig, ax = plt.subplots(1, 2*len(allMasses), figsize = (25, 4))
            for iii, masses in enumerate(allMasses):
                lim = max(freqs)
                ax[2*iii].plot(kk[coords[iii][:,1]], oo[coords[iii][:,0]], 'o', ms=5, label='valid points')
                ax[2*iii].plot(kk, np.sqrt(omega_fit(kk,masses[-1])), label=f'$m^2 = %5.5f$'%(masses[-1]))
                ax[2*iii].set_title(title[iii]+f'$T = %5.2f, \gamma = %5.2f, \lambda = %5.2f$'%(list_temp[tem], list_gamma[gam], list_lamb[lam]))
                ax[2*iii].axhline(masses[-1], color='darkgray', ls=':', label='best fit')

                [op.set_xlim(-lim,lim) for op in ax[::2]]
                [op.set_ylim(0,lim) for op in ax[::2]]

                lim = 5
                ax[2*iii+1].plot(kk, np.sqrt(omega_fit(kk,masses[-1])), color = 'y', label=f'$m^2 = %5.5f$'%(masses[-1]))
                im = ax[2*iii+1].imshow(PowSpecs[iii], aspect='auto', interpolation='none', origin='lower', extent=[kk[0],kk[-1],oo[0],oo[-1]])
                clb = plt.colorbar(im, ax = ax[2*iii+1])

                [opp.set_xlabel(r'$\bar{k}$') for opp in ax[1::2]]
                [opp.set_ylabel(r'$\bar{\omega_k}$') for opp in ax[1::2]]
                [opp.set_xlim(-lim,lim) for opp in ax[1::2]]
                [opp.set_ylim(0,lim) for opp in ax[1::2]]
                [opp.axvline(0, color='white', ls=':') for opp in ax[1::2]]
            [op.legend(loc='upper center') for op in ax]
            plt.show()
    return allMasses

multiplier = 10
gam = 0

colors = cycle(('b', 'g', 'orange', 'r', 'm', 'k'))
title = ['Full, ', 'Real, ', 'Imag, ']
for lam in range(len(list_lamb)):
    col = next(colors)
    allMasses = get_masses_seps(False, multiplier, lam, gam)
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(1, len(allMasses), figsize=(25, 4))

    for iii, masses in enumerate(allMasses):
        ax[iii].plot(list_temp, masses, marker='o', linestyle='None', color=col, label=title[iii]+f'$\gamma = %5.2f, \lambda = %5.2f$'%(list_gamma[gam], list_lamb[lam]))

    for ijk in ax:
        list_m2_eff_at_nTime = np.abs(np.asarray([(-m2eff if list_gamma[gam] == 1 else m2eff) + 0.5*list_lamb[lam]*np.mean(all_data[tem][lam][gam][:,0,-1]**2.) for tem in range(len(list_temp))]))
        ijk.plot(list_temp, list_m2_eff_at_nTime, color=col, linestyle='-.', label='prediction for $t=t_f$')
        ijk.plot(list_temp, np.abs(th_masses(list_lamb[lam], list_gamma[gam], np.asarray(list_temp))), ':', color=col, label='prediction from PS')

    [jk.axhline(m2eff, color='darkgray', ls='--', label='potential mass') for jk in ax]
    [jk.set_title(f'multiplier = %5.0f, $\gamma = %5.2f, \lambda = %5.2f$'%(multiplier, list_gamma[gam], list_lamb[lam])) for jk in ax]
    [jk.set_ylabel(f'$m^2(T, \gamma, \lambda)$') for jk in ax]
    [jk.set_xlabel(f'$T$') for jk in ax]
    [jk.set_yscale('log') for jk in ax]
    [jk.legend() for jk in ax]
    plt.show()
